    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a condensed lineup, as core stars like **Yordan Alvarez**, **Junior Caminero**, **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, and **Trea Turner** are sidelined due to scheduled off-days. Consequently, the offense hinges on the table-setting prowess of **Colt Keith** (66.33) and **Chase Meidroth** (62.08), our two strongest plays. **Colt Keith** benefits from a high-leverage leadoff spot and a favorable matchup against Mick Abel, whose 4.28 xERA offers a solid platform for counting stats. Similarly, **Chase Meidroth** gains significant utility from favorable wind conditions and a matchup against Seth Lugo; his ability to catalyze the offense out of the #1 slot is vital while we navigate the absence of **Kyle Schwarber**, **Christian Yelich**, and **Victor Scott II**.\n\nDown the order, we are exercising caution with **Dillon Dingler** (43.85) and **Carson Benge** (42.63). **Dillon Dingler** faces a moderate drag from his projected #6 spot and a dynamic platoon disadvantage, keeping him in marginal territory. **Carson Benge** represents the most precarious start of the day; his 42.63 score is suppressed by a difficult L/L platoon matchup against Eduardo Rodriguez and a bottom-tier batting order assignment. While **Caleb Durbin**, **Hyeseong Kim**, **Kazuma Okamoto**, **Zac Veen**, **Lars Nootbaar**, **Logan O'Hoppe**, **Josh Smith**, **Jerar Encarnacion**, and **Luis Pena** are not in action today, the decision to start **Carson Benge** over a potential pinch-hit candidate remains strictly volume-based to manage our game caps. If the official lineups materialize with further shifts in the batting order, specifically if **Dillon Dingler** is pushed out of the six-hole, we will re-evaluate our pinch-hit strategy to prioritize speed-heavy options that help us maintain our edge in the stolen base category.",
